<br>
Why I like them:<br>
a) Plenty of spawns in one spot. Never had to search for the next pull.<br>
b) They are all close enough to the same level that you only see blues at 45. A good amount of light blues at 51, but some blues.<br>
c) Just around the corner from the wizzie/nexus spire. Bind in bazaar, port down when you ready to hunt.  Great for the mage who doesn't have a port whore on call.<br>
d) My friend says he hasn't seen anyone else hunting these (on Rallos Zek).<br>
e) Safe medding/downtime. Sit near the grass outside the spire and there are you will be no where near the 1 or 2 roamers that walk by the outside.<br>
f) No overpulls. They follow a path that has them stop in the corners of the room, where they will bunch up, but they go from the corners single.  Pull them when the walk to a new corner. They seem to have a small aggro radius as well (like the yetis?).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
They have more hp and hit harder than bloodgills, but they are much easier to pull, and they aren't anywhere near as camped. The many benefits of fighting them makes me wish I had had them when I was 45. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzyromz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZyromZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(3/16/02 10:37:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: plaugebone thief</span><hr size=1> yup these are great was kinda tough at 43 gettign 44 but in 3 kills average i made a blue<br>
