<br>
I came here at the weekend at 47, and now I'm close to dinging 49.<br>
<br>
On my server, this place can be quite busy, but it's mainly occupied by soloers.  There were 3 there yesterday, but there were plenty of skellys for everyone.<br>
<br>
My tactic was park just in front of the entrance at the base of the pyramid opposite - /pet guard here.<br>
<br>
The skellys roam around the inside of the building and you can seem them easily enough.  I pulled with Mal (these guys are NOT social.  There can be 6 of em all grouped together and they won't join in).<br>
<br>
Set pet on skelly just as it runs out the building, let it build up some hate then elemental maelstrom.  That's it! No more nuking required.<br>
<br>
I used firepet, but I really, really recommend giving him full set of plate, 2 daggers and elemental defender (the daggers are only there to force the defender onto his back).  In my first encounter (without armour), I had to cast 2 heals on pet to keep it alive.  With armour, you needn't worry about it.<br>
<br>
I also found that this is a good place to beef up your meleeing and defence.  When mob is down to 2 bubs of health, I stepped in and flailed wildly, mainly to get my defense up, but also to improve my 1hb.  At 2 bubs it gives you just enough wacks before it turns around and runs.<br>
<br>
Loot is crap. 5pp at the most.  Has dropped some words (Convocation) and a monk quest item I think (research notes page 6).<br>
<br>
Experience is great!<br>
<br>
Oh yeah - the wandering skellys are easy enough, BUT watch out for that Wraithbone Champion.  He conned DB to me (like the rest), and I thought I'd give him a go.  I chaincast about 6-7 pets and this guy still didn't die.  He had a very high MR and none of my spells stuck.  I had to gate in the end.  I then grouped up with another soloer (Shammy) and we took him down between us, but I was OOM at the end of it!<br>
<br>
Canelin.<br>
