e>   Re: plaugebone thief</span><hr size=1> Just a bump for a great solo camp. I usually grab a C3 and a port to DL. Most people will split the camp with you, and it won't be long before you will have it all to yourself. I have dinged 46, 47, and 46 here. Nice and easy single pulls, safe medding, and enough plat drops to pay for my C and port. <br>
<br>
Here is how I do it. <br>
<br>
1. Summon 44 fire pet and buff with burnout 2, hand 2 summoned daggers. (yep, I think armor and stuff slows them down)<br>
2. Set pet guarding at the SIDE of the pyramid right in front of the one with the skellies. <br>
3. Go up, target a thief, (watch for spurbones/Wraithbone champion wanderers, wander around pyramid, but not around the one you pet is sitting next to) Blast with Maliesment or (I prefer) Elemental Malstrom. Watch it come back, sic pet, pet should be able to pull aggro right off, you shouldn't get hit at all. <br>
4. DONT SIT or you will pull aggro with the dot stuck to the skelly. Watch, and either heal pet if needed, or SoS skelly at 50% life, or even a blaze. This should set the skelly to near 20% life, and running. Sit and med, bring pet back, /pet sit and then med, or heal pet and repeat. <br>
<br>
I can clear the pyramid and the wanderers by medding for about 30-45 secs with pet sitting/regening health, and I will be OOM, but will have no spawns. Med to 80% or so, and they will start repopping in the pyramid. 1% XP per kill at 47, haven't killed them in 48 yet. (just dinged today, C3 was gone for the last few, and had to log for work)<br>
<br>
If you want a bit more loot, maybe go to KC and hope for lucky rolls. (I can't roll worth a dang, I have never won a roll in 20 levels)<br>
XP is much slower grouped in KC, but some nice loot drops there, which can be sold. <br>
